dct_description_sm: Relief shown by contours, hachures, and spot heights.
"Vertical interval: 25 metres. 5 metre intervals ... are only approximate."
Normal and narrow gauge railroads, seven classes of roads and tracks, two types of internal boundaries, and various types of vegetation are indicated.
Based on maps by the Istituto geografico militare.

Set includes various issues of some sheets; some reproduced by 512 (A. Fd. Svy.) Coy., RE.; some by units of British Middle East Forces (M.D.R. 343); some by units of British Eights Army (W.D.R. 343); some reissued by U.S. Army Map Service with series designation: Provisional G.S.G.S. 3980.
Marginal maps: Index to adjoining sheets and to grids -- Reliability diagram.
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain, War Office., General Staff., Geographical Section.
Great Britain, Army., Royal Engineers., Fd. Survey Coy., 512.
